Press Windows+R  
Type diskmamt.msc and press Enter 
select "c Drive" & right click 
Select option shrink volume 
Enter amount to be shrink e.g "10" 
An unallocated pantition will be created 
Select the unallocated vol. (which we created) 80 right click on it 
Select "New simple Volume 
Welcome wizard appears Next 
Assign Drive Lettel (e.g. C, D,E), Clict Next 
Select File system as NTFS 
Conformation Wizard woud appear & click Finish
